  "text": "The 2-form gauge field B  in this case is seen to behave like a WZ field and the term involving this field is seen to behave like a WZ term for the CGFPD1BA which, in the absence of this term, is seen to possess a set of second-class constraints and consequently describe a GNI theory which does not respect the local gauge symmetries defined by the WSRI and WI given by Equation [CITATION_1] .",
